By INNOCENT ODOH | The federal government has again extended the deadline for National Identity Number (NIN)-SIM data verification from May 6 to June 30, 2021 following demand from stakeholders to make it easier for Nigerian citizens and residents to obtain and link their NINs. This was disclosed in a joint statement issued yesterday by the director, public affairs at Nigerian Communications Commission (NCC), Dr Ikechukwu Adinde, and the head, corporate communications at National Identity Management Commission (NIMC), Mr Kayode Adegoke, stressing that the NIN enrolment has reached 54 million. The statement noted that the decision to extend the date was reached at a virtual meeting chaired by the minister of communications and digital economy, Dr Isa Ibrahim Pantami.